	<div id="content">
		<a name="top" id="top"></a>
		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Differences between Spanish and Portuguese</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<p><b><a href="/wiki/Portuguese_language" title="Portuguese language">Portuguese</a></b> and <b><a href="/wiki/Spanish_language" title="Spanish language">Spanish</a></b> are among the most widely spoken languages in the world today. Although they are closely related, to the point of having a noticeable degree of <a href="/wiki/Mutual_intelligibility" title="Mutual intelligibility">mutual intelligibility</a>, there are also important differences between them, which can pose difficulties for people acquainted with one of the languages who attempt to learn the other. Both are part of a broader group known as <a href="/wiki/West_Iberian_languages" title="West Iberian languages">West Iberian</a>, which contains also several minor languages or dialects with fewer speakers, all of which are mutually intelligible among themselves to some degree.</p>
<div class="noprint tright portal" style="border:solid #aaa 1px;margin:0.5em 0 0.5em 0.5em;">
<table style="background:#f9f9f9; font-size:85%; line-height:110%;">
<tr>
<td><a href="/wiki/File:Portal.svg" class="image" title="Portal.svg"><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c9/Portal.svg/28px-Portal.svg.png" width="28" height="28" border="0" /></a></td>
<td style="padding:0 0.2em;"><i><b><a href="/wiki/Portal:Language" title="Portal:Language">Language portal</a></b></i></td>
</tr>
</table>
</div>
<p>There are also some significant differences between <a href="/wiki/Brazilian_Portuguese" title="Brazilian Portuguese">Brazilian</a> and <a href="/wiki/European_Portuguese" title="European Portuguese">European Portuguese</a>. This article notes these differences below only where:</p>
<ul>
<li>Both Brazilian <i>and</i> European Portuguese differ not only from each other, but from Spanish as well</li>
<li>Either Brazilian <i>or</i> European Portuguese differs from Spanish with <a href="/wiki/Syntax" title="Syntax">syntax</a> not possible in Spanish (while the other dialect does not)</li>
</ul>
<p><br /></p>
<table class="infobox" cellpadding="3" style="clear: right; width: 27em; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 83%; line-height: 1.2em">
<tr>
<td style="vertical-align: middle"><b>This article contains <a href="/wiki/International_Phonetic_Alphabet" title="International Phonetic Alphabet">IPA</a> phonetic symbols.</b> Without proper <a href="/wiki/Wikipedia:IPA" title="Wikipedia:IPA">rendering support</a>, you may see <a href="/wiki/Mojibake" title="Mojibake">question marks, boxes, or other symbols</a> instead of <a href="/wiki/Unicode" title="Unicode">Unicode</a> characters.</td>
</tr>
</table>
